{
  "page": "Emperor of Valyria",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Emperor of Valyria</b> was the title claimed by <a href=\"/index.php/Aurion\" title=\"Aurion\">Aurion</a>, one of the few <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonlords\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragonlords\">dragonlords</a> who survived the <a href=\"/index.php/Doom_of_Valyria\" title=\"Doom of Valyria\">Doom of Valyria</a>, according to histories of <a href=\"/index.php/Qohor\" title=\"Qohor\">Qohor</a>. Aurion was the only one to hold the title as, according to these aforementioned histories, Emperor Aurion flew atop his <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> followed by thirty thousand men to claim what remained of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a> and reestablish the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_Freehold\" title=\"Valyrian Freehold\">Freehold</a> only for him and his host to never be seen again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Emperor_of_Valyria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &am